  "prompt": "Help me develop a GELU activation operator (tanh / Pad\u00e9 approximation form) that supports float32 data type. The shape is mainly [1,128], [4,2048], [32,4096]. GELU(x) = 0.5*x*(1+tanh(sqrt(2/pi)*(x+0.044715*x^3))). Use asc2.tanh; do NOT use asc2.erf (simulator erf is too noisy on float32). CRITICAL: when multiplying a Tile by a Python scalar inside the @asc2.jit body, the Tile MUST be on the LEFT (write `x_cubed * 0.044715`, NOT `0.044715 * x_cubed`). The asc2 Tile class does not implement __rmul__, so scalar-on-left raises AttributeError at codegen time. Compute sqrt(2/pi) and 0.044715 as Python module-level constants outside the @asc2.jit function. For host-side reference, use np.tanh. Use np.testing.assert_allclose(out, expected, atol=1e-2, rtol=1e-2).",
